                <h1>Understanding Background Extinction Rates: A Critical Insight</h1>
                <p>The rate of background extinctions per year is estimated to be about 1 to 5 species per million species. This rate is a natural occurrence, but current human activities have accelerated extinction rates, leading to a biodiversity crisis. Conservation efforts are vital to protect endangered species and maintain ecological balance.</p>
